{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/2543","id":3748502314,"node_id":"PR_kwDOEHbxG87fbZsq","html_url":"https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/pull/2543","diff_url":"https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/pull/2543.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/pull/2543.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/issues/2543","number":2543,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"Decompile grCastle_801CE19C","user":{"login":"Erotemic","id":3186211,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxODYyMTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3186211?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic","html_url":"https://github.com/Erotemic","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erotemic/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"Getting my feet wet on this. This replaces a small bit of ASM with equivalent C code, and the generated bytes match 100%. Removing the tmp variables seemed necessary. I tried a few nicer looking variants but that kept regressing. This is the nicest one that worked. The bulk of the work was done with a GPT 5.5 chat interface. I drove it, suggested strategies, and gave feedback to comply with the AI policy. My perspective on this is purely mechanical, but I did ask it what this function is likely for, and its thoughts seemed reasonable:\r\n\r\n> My best guess: grCastle_801CE19C is a one-shot/timer-driven castle-stage object spawner or state-transition handler.\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n\r\n> More concretely, it looks like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nif castle9.xDE high bit is set:\r\n      decrement castle9.xD4 timer\r\n      when the timer expires:\r\n          create / fetch another ground object\r\n          clear the high-bit flag in xDE\r\n          if the new object exists:\r\n              do follow-up initialization/linking\r\n```\r\n\r\n> The important clues are:\r\n\r\n> gp->gv.castle9.xDE >> 7 & 1 is checking the high bit of xDE. That looks like an “armed / pending / active” flag.\r\n\r\n> xD4 is treated as a signed countdown timer. It reads the old value into timer, stores timer - 1, then checks if (timer < 0). That means the action triggers once the countdown has gone negative.\r\n\r\n> grCastle_801CE054(gobj) + 8 looks like it is computing an index or variant ID, then offsetting it by 8.\r\n\r\n> grCastle_801CD4D0(...) returns an HSD_GObj*, so it is likely creating, locating, or activating another castle-related ground object.\r\n\r\n> The bitfield write is clearing the same high bit that gated the whole function. In other words, after the trigger fires, it disables the pending flag so this does not keep spawning every frame.\r\n\r\n</details>","created_at":"2026-05-26T13:42:40Z","updated_at":"2026-05-26T17:43:33Z","closed_at":"2026-05-26T17:43:33Z","merged_at":"2026-05-26T17:43:33Z","merge_commit_sha":"c75e4117053da384d314fe69f7c72f9a48dd6c59","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/2543/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/2543/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/issues/2543/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/statuses/545c43a